    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Greek archaic rudely carved cult statues, originally of wood, and later copied in stone. Scholarship suggests that only stone or marble copies of originals in wood have survived to the present day.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
